	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To make your specialization go up, you DO NOT NEED to put 1 point in all of the specializations.  I am a 35 wizzie and put 1 point in Alteration and 5 points in Evocation.  I then casted a 1st lvl fire-based evocation spell upon myself and it started going up.  It currently sits at 108 and still going.  Clerics that are specializing in healing, the easiest way to get it going up is to cast your lowest lvl heal on anyone that needs a heal.  DO NOT CAST on anyone that is full health.  My friend did this for hours and never once did it go up.  Now if it stopped raising, then throw another practice point if possible in that specialization or another one, just 1 will do, and practice again.  I did this to my friends cleric and it worked.  Her specialization is now at 99.  Any questions contact me on the Quelious Server.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
