	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Whichever stat you reach 50 in 1st will be the one that you specialize in. All of the specializations can be trained up to 50 and the one skill that you reached 50 in 1st can be trained higher.<BR>
<BR>
If you reach 50 1st in evocation then you can train evocation specialization more than 50. If you reach 50 1st in alteration then you can train alteration specialization more than 50. All of the other specializations can only go to 50.<BR>
<BR>
The amount of points that can be trained per level in a skill is based on the formula (your level * 5 + 5). So a level 8 would be 8 * 5 + 5 = 45...so as early as level 9 your specialization could be decided based on that formula. 9 * 5 + 5 = 50.<BR>
<BR>
I have a wizard and some spells raise 2 skills, I've seen ice spells raise both my alteration and my evocation. Not knowing that I had to have the skill that I wanted to specialize in reach 50 first, I didn't pay attention and my alteration hit 50 before my evocation. I wanted my evocation to be my specialization and I had to buy the guy a ruby to get it changed. ***The guy asks for a ruby and after I gave it to him he said, 'did you bring the 25pp I asked for?' He never mentioned the pp before. Not having the money I think I gave him 5pp, but my specialization was changed.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
